claire rosenbaum transformative learning technologies laboratory home about publications projects people teaching media fablearn 2011 home people claire rosenbaum claire rosenbaum position visiting researchers claire rosenbaum graduated from stanford's product design program mechanical engineering bs in 2010 which had a large focus on the human centered design process during her undergraduate career claire interned at the children's discovery museum of san jose and collaborated with the exploratorium in san francisco for a class claire has continued her work in the field of science education by enthusiastically serving as the lab and education programs manager in the tltlab claire continues her efforts in science education by tutoring with stanford's science in service program which brings science activities to the students of local boys and girls clubs on weekends claire attends outings with the bay area emerging museum professionals baemp and generally enjoys life as a wisconsin transplant living in san francisco people faculty visiting researchers phd students ma students ms students undergraduate students high school interns collaborators alumni transformative learning technologies lab school of education stanford university 520 galvez mall room 102 ceras building stanford california 94305 usa connect with us connect with us on facebook connect with us on twitter connect with us on youtube connect with us on flickr copyright 2011 all rights reserved top
